From 16bb710cb5227c35d170e4ebba0d9a8ed032b103 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: rockbox-hiby-r1-ci <ci@example.invalid>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 19:15:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] hibyr1: keep bluetooth active across handoff; enable
 bootloader logging

Two bootloader (hibyos_linux.c) changes for the R1:

1. Drop HIBY_R1 from the bt_suspend-on-boot guard so Bluetooth stays
   active across the bootloader -> Rockbox handoff (BT IS supported here).

2. Enable ENABLE_LOGGING. The bootloader then redirects its stdout/stderr
   to BASE_DIR/rockbox.log, and the BOOT_ROCKBOX path execve()s the
   Rockbox binary WITHOUT closing those fds, so Rockbox inherits them.
   rb_backtrace prints crash backtraces to stdout, so a segfault is now
   captured to /data/mnt/sd_0/rockbox.log for post-mortem instead of only
   flashing on /dev/console. Pairs with shipping the unstripped
   rockbox.elf for addr2line symbolication.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 bootloader/hibyos_linux.c | 10 +++++++---
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/bootloader/hibyos_linux.c b/bootloader/hibyos_linux.c
index edda204796..ce43bb1e3f 100644
--- a/bootloader/hibyos_linux.c
+++ b/bootloader/hibyos_linux.c
@@ -47,7 +47,11 @@
 #include <stdarg.h>
 #include "version.h"
 
-//#define ENABLE_LOGGING
+/* Enabled on the R1 so the bootloader redirects stdout/stderr to
+ * BASE_DIR/rockbox.log. The Rockbox binary is exec'd with these fds
+ * inherited, so its crash backtrace (rb_backtrace prints to stdout) is
+ * captured to a file for post-mortem instead of only hitting /dev/console. */
+#define ENABLE_LOGGING
 //#define AUTO_ENABLE_ADB
 
 /* Basic configuration */
@@ -694,8 +698,8 @@ int main(int argc, char **argv)
         }
         else if(mode == BOOT_ROCKBOX)
         {
-#if defined(HIBY_R3PROII) || defined(HIBY_R1)
-            /* Suspend bluetooth as it's not currently supported */
+#if defined(HIBY_R3PROII)
+            /* Suspend bluetooth before booting Rockbox. */
             system("/usr/bin/bt_suspend");
 #endif
             fflush(stdout);
